.TH LEO 1 "March 2026" "1.0" "Leo Language Manual"
.SH NAME
leo \- high-performance JIT-based execution environment for the Leo language
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B leo
[\fIfile.leo\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B leo
is the primary command-line interface for the Leo programming language. It
functions as an interpreter that utilizes a Just-In-Time (JIT) compiler to
dynamically optimize and execute code on the fly.
.PP
Source files are processed sequentially. If no files are provided, the
program exits without taking any action.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I file.leo
A source file to be executed. The VM will load and dynamically compile the
contents for immediate execution.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success. All files were executed.
.TP
.B 1
Failure. A syntax error or runtime exception occurred.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR luajit (1),
.BR node (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Developed by Michał Pociecha-Łoś.
